When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work
local?

     This is useful when you want to share the code with different people or as a place to keep track of your code .

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?

    This may lead to a lot of unnecessary files being commited which we might not want to.
    Sometimes it may commit for a more than one logical change performed .

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.  When would you
use one instead of another?

    We might want to have the copy of someone else's repository , forking should be done .
    But if we want to have a copy of a repository in your local device then we should clone .
    A branch is used for working on a new experimental feature which you are not sure about.

